<FIRST>r a PM-WeatherpageWeather     10-16 0509</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0521</SECOND>
<HEAD>Hurricane Jerry Hits Texas Coast</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Remnants of Hurricane Jerry drenched Texas today after the storm
roared ashore in Galveston with sustained winds of 80 mph and gusts
to 100 mph.
   Before withering into a tropical depression early today, Jerry
spun off a half-dozen tornadoes inland, blacked out at least 52,000
homes and businesses and cut off phone service to Galveston Island.
   Tides along the Gulf Coast were 5 to 8 feet above normal as
Jerry's landfall coincided with an unusually high tide caused by a
rare alignment of the Earth, moon and sun. But Gary Vasquez of the
Galveston emergency operations center reported only minor street
flooding.
   Elsewhere, severe storms produced a tornado and large hail in
northern Michigan on Sunday. The tornado touched down in Buckley,
on Michigan's northern Lower Peninsula, knocking down trees and
destroying at least one mobile home, said Sgt. Marty Dahlstrom of
the Wexford County Sheriff's Department said
   The Michigan storms produced wind gusts to 85 mph and hail as
large as ping-pong balls, the National Weather Service said.
   Snow fell this morning in the higher elevations of Colorado and
Wyoming.
   Showers and a few thunderstorms were reported in central
Wisconsin and southeastern Minnesota. Light showers extended across
central Minnesota into central South Dakota.
   High temperatures Sunday were in the 40s from northern Minnesota
to the northern half of the high Plains and in the 30s in the
central Rocky Mountains. Temperatures reached the 90s in parts of
Florida, Texas and the desert Southwest. Records were tied in
Baltimore, 89, and Kansas City, 84.
   Other reports at 3 a.m. EDT:
   _East: Albany, N.Y. 57 drizzle; Atlanta 68 fair; Boston 53
drizzle; Charleston, S.C. 69 foggy; Chattanooga 62 foggy;
Cincinnati 61 fair; Cleveland 62 fair; Detroit 59 fair; Hatteras 62
foggy; Jacksonville 72 foggy; Key West 83 fair; Knoxville 59 fair;
Macon 67 partly cloudy; Miami 79 fair; New York 60 foggy;
Philadelphia 62 foggy; Pittsburgh 59 fair; Portland, Maine 53
foggy; Richmond 61 foggy; Tampa 74 fair; Washington, D.C. 63 foggy.
   _Central: Birmingham 71 fair; Bismarck 40 cloudy; Chicago 67
partly cloudy; Denver 34 snow; Des Moines 50 thunderstorms;
Indianapolis 59 fair; Kansas City 69 partly cloudy; Little Rock 70
fair; Louisville 60 fair; Memphis 73 fair; Nashville 69 fair; New
Orleans 76 foggy; North Platte 38 rain; Oklahoma City 67 cloudy;
Omaha 48 showers; Rapid City 33 cloudy; St. Louis 67 fair;
Minneapolis-St. Paul 48 cloudy; Sault Ste. Marie 50 rain; San
Antonio 64 fair.
   _West: Albuquerque 55 cloudy; Anchorage 37 rain; Boise 36 fair;
Casper 32 snow; Fairbanks 34 cloudy; Great Falls 31 fair; Honolulu
76 fair; Las Vegas 65 fair; Los Angeles 60 fair; Medford 43 fair;
Pendleton 37 fair; Phoenix 74 fair; Portland, Ore. 46 partly
cloudy; Reno 46 cloudy; Salt Lake City 45 fair; San Diego 63 fair;
San Francisco 51 cloudy; Seattle 46 partly cloudy; Spokane 37 fair.
   _International: Calgary 30 partly cloudy; Montreal 50 showers;
Ottawa 50 thunderstorms; Regina 30 partly cloudy; Toronto 48 foggy;
Winnipeg 32 partly cloudy.
