<TEXT>
   A preacher was stung to death by a swarm
of bees that invaded a church service in central Nigeria, Radio
Nigeria reported Monday.
   Scores of worshipers were stung in the incident Sunday while
fleeing the swarm, which flew into the church after a farmer
disturbed their hive at Ipee in Kwara state, the broadcast said.
   Joseph Ogubayoma, 40, an elder of the Cherubim and Seraphim
evangelical church, was stung to death when he tried to drive the
bees away with a broom.
