<HEAD>Soviet Jet Catches Fire in Nigeria, Only Minor Injuries</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LAGOS, Nigeria (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Soviet jetliner carrying 180 people
caught fire at Lagos' airport while preparing to take off, but all
aboard were evacuated with only minor injuries, airport sources
said Monday.
   Yuri Kouphakor, the Soviet ambassador to Nigeria, was among
those injured while leaving the smoking Aeroflot Tupelov 154 at
Murtala Muhammed International Airport on Saturday, according to
the sources, who declined to be further identified.
   The plane had taxied to the runway and was preparing to take off
for Moscow when two of its engines caught fire, the sources said.
   It took firefighters more than 20 minutes to put out the blaze.
No other details were available.
