<HEAD>Soviets Give Honorary Degree to Former West German Chancellor</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MOSCOW (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Moscow State University gave former West German
Chancellor Willy Brandt an honorary degree and a medal naming him a
professor emeritus Monday for his efforts to promote friendship
among nations.
   Brandt, who led his country from 1969 to 1974, was praised for
his efforts to end the nuclear arms race.
   The 75-year-old honorary chairman of the West German Social
Democratic Party also dined with Politburo member Alexander
Yakovlev Sunday and met Monday with Soviet political scientists.
