<FIRST>r w AM-China-Corn     10-16 0099</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-China-Corn,100</SECOND>
<HEAD>China Buys U.S. Corn</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   China has bought 150,000 metric tons of U.S.
corn for delivery in the 1989-90 marketing year that began on Sept.
1, the first in two years, the Agriculture Department said Monday.
   China bought large quantities of U.S. wheat last year but has
not imported corn since 1987-88, according to department records.
   A metric ton is about 2,205 pounds and is equal to 39.4 bushels
of corn. The new sale would be about 5.9 million bushels and would
have a U.S. farm value of around $13 million at recent prices.
</TEXT>
