<FIRST>r f BC-CoalProduction     10-16 0108</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Coal Production,0114</SECOND>
<HEAD>Industry Reports Weekly Production</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHARLESTON, W.Va. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Domestic coal production totaled 20.1
million short tons during the week ending Oct. 7, down slightly
from the 20.3 million short tons produced in the previous week, the
Department of Energy reported Monday.
   The U.S. coal industry produced 19 million short tons in the
same week last year, according to the department's Energy
Information Administration.
   A short ton is equal to 2,000 pounds.
   Domestic coal production so far this year is 740.2 million short
tons, 5.8 percent above last year's production at this time, the
agency said.
   The week's production accounts for bituminous and lignite coal.
</TEXT>
