<FIRST>r f AM-Earns-TRW     10-16 0183</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Earns-TRW,0191</SECOND>
<HEAD>TRW Sales Up, Earnings Down</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CLEVELAND (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   TRW Inc. earnings declined 11 percent in the
third quarter completed Sept. 30, although sales were up 8 percent,
the company reported Monday.
   TRW, which provides products and services for the space and
defense, automotive and information systems markets, earned $60
million, or 98 cents per share, on sales of $1.79 billion in the
quarter.
   In the third quarter of 1988, TRW earned $68 million, or $1.11 a
share, when sales were $1.65 billion. That period, however,
included a divestitutre gain principally from th sale of Reda Pump
and Oilwell Cable businesses.
   The company reported its biggest gain in its information systems
segment, where sales climbed 44 percent to $196 million, from $135
million in the year-ago period. Acquisition of Chilton Corp.
accounted for half the increase.
   Through nine months, sales were up 3 percent to $5.42 billion,
and earnings were down 3 percent, to $199 million, or $3.22 per
share. In the first nine months of 1988, the company earned $205
million or $3.33 a share on sales of $5.27 billion.
