<HEAD>Prices Slide</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The energy futures market ended lower Monday,
with moderate losses sustained in crude oil and refined petroleum
products.
   On the New York Mercantile Exchange, the November contract for
West Texas Intermediate, the benchmark grade of U.S. crude oil,
slid 30 cents to settle at $20.59 a 42-gallon barrel, after rising
42 cents on Friday.
   Other contract months also fell.
   Among other refined petroleum products traded on the New York
Merc, the November contract for wholesale home heating oil lost
0.45 cent to close at 60.42 cents a gallon. The contract had
declined 0.30 cent on Friday.
   November unleaded gasoline, which rose 0.58 cent in the previous
session, fell 0.30 cent to 55.85 cents a gallon.
