<FIRST>d f BC-SavingsBonds     10-16 0114</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Savings Bonds,0119</SECOND>
<HEAD>Sales Up in September</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Sales of U.S. Savings Bonds totaled $528
million in September, up 2 percent from the same month a year ago,
the Treasury Department reported Monday.
   The September sales raised the total of bonds sold in fiscal
1989, which ended Sept. 30, to $7.72 billion, the most since 1987
and 6 percent above the total in 1988.
   The Treasury said Americans held a record $115.7 billion worth
of bonds at the end of September.
   The government raised the interest rate on bonds to 7.81 percent
from 7.35 last May 1. The current rate is effective through Oct. 31
when held five years or longer.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
