<FILEID>AP-NR-10-16-89 2331EDT</FILEID>
<FIRST>r f BC-Earns-McClatchy     10-16 0195</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Earns-McClatchy,0205</SECOND>
<HEAD>McClatchy Newspapers Report Earnings Up 21 Percent in Third Quarter</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SACRAMENTO, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   McClatchy Newspapers reported Monday a
21.5 percent increase in net income for its third quarter compared
to the same period last year.
   It said third-quarter profit reached $8.8 million, 31 cents a
share, compared with $7.2 million, or 25 cents a share, in the
third quarter of 1988.
   McClatchy said revenue grew 7.5 percent during the third quarter
to $94.9 million compared with $88.3 million during the same period
of 1988.
   Advertising revenue grew 7.2 percent to $75.3 million in the
third quarter, and circulation revenue jumped 9.2 percent to $16
million.
   Third-quarter operating income rose 14.5 percent to $13.8
million from last year's $12.1 million.
   The company cited as major contributors to the increase in
quarterly operating income the improved margins at the Tacoma News
Tribune and the Anchorage Daily News, and continued favorable
newsprint prices.
   McClatchy announced last month an agreement to buy three
dailies, four weeklies and a monthly from The News and Observer
Publishing Co. of Raleigh, N.C., for $74.1 million.
   Sacramento-based McClatchy publishes 13 newspapers, including
six dailies, in California, Washington and Alaska.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
